The paper discusses technical issues related to protocols and security, which are typically covered in the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses issues related to formalizations of informational monies, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also touches on legal, psychological, and ethical aspects of informational money, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper discusses the economical merits and outlooks for Bitcoin, which could fall under cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
